        'NUMBERS: Probability dealer has BJ when showing Ace: in 1 deck = 16/51 = 31.37%. In 6 decks = 96/311 = 30.87%. True odds needed for even bet: 33.33% (2:1 payout means breakeven at 33.33% probability). Since actual probability (30.87-31.37%) is below 33.33%, the insurance bet has negative EV. House edge on insurance: (30.87% x 2) - (69.13% x 1) = -7.39% in 6 decks. For every $10 insurance bet, expected loss = $0.74.',
