        'DEFINITION: Dealer rules dictate whether the dealer must hit or stand on soft 17 (a hand containing an Ace counted as 11 totalling 17, such as A,6). S17 = Stand on ALL 17s. H17 = Hit on soft 17.',
        'DETAILED RULES: S17: dealer stands on hard 17 (10,7) AND soft 17 (A,6). H17: dealer hits A,6 (soft 17) but stands on hard 17 (10,7). If dealer hits soft 17 and the new card creates another soft 17 (e.g., A,6,3 = soft 20? No — A,6 draws 3 = A,6,3 = 20 soft, stand. A,6 draws Ace = A,6,A = 18 soft, stand. A,6 draws 4 = 21, stand). The only hit-on-soft-17 continuation is when the hand remains a soft 17 (rare: A,6, A,6,A cannot happen since A would make soft 18). Dealer does not hit soft 18 or above.',
        'NUMBERS: H17 adds exactly 0.22% to house edge compared to S17. S17 player basic strategy: standing 12 vs dealer 2. H17 adjustment: hitting 17 vs dealer Ace (basic strategy changes for H17 are minimal). Dealer bust probability in S17: 28.4% overall. Dealer bust probability in H17: 29.6% (slightly higher because dealer hits soft 17 more). The dealer\'s extra hit on soft 17 improves dealer\'s hand about 70% of the time (making 18-21), hurts about 30% (busting).',
        'STRATEGIC MEANING: H17 benefits the casino because the dealer\'s soft 17 improves more often than it busts. Players should seek S17 tables (usually higher minimum bets). H17 subtly changes basic strategy: 11 vs Ace should double in H17 (EV -0.09 vs S17 becomes... still negative but less bad). A,7 vs dealer Ace in H17: stand vs S17, hit vs H17. Players adjust strategy slightly for H17 tables.',
