        'DEFINITION: Blackjack (natural 21 on first two cards) traditionally pays 3:2 (1.5 times the bet). Some modern tables pay 6:5 (1.2x) or even 1:1 (even money), drastically increasing the house edge.',
        'DETAILED RULES: 3:2 means for every $2 bet, you win $3 (payout = 1.5x). 6:5 means for every $5 bet, you win $6 (payout = 1.2x). 1:1 means even money (payout = 1.0x). The bet is paid in addition to the original bet being returned. Only a natural 2-card Ace + 10-value counts as blackjack; a 21 achieved by hitting or splitting is not a blackjack and pays 1:1.',
